s clarified. Numerical results show that if the incident shock wave intensity\nis high enough, the focusing zone of the reflected expansion wave can be\nidentified as a cavity inside the droplet. Furthermore, the cavitation zone is\nenlarged, and the stronger collapsing waves are induced by increasing the\nincident shock wave intensity.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 1 May 2022 14:04:04 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sat, 18 Mar 2023 14:32:48 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-03-21"}
